President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Colorado and has ordered federal aid to assist with recovery efforts from the Black Forest Fire that occurred from June 11-21, 2013. The federal funding will be used for crisis counseling, disaster unemployment assistance, emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Thomas J. McCool has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.